---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const base = '/GoswickRanchMayerArizona';
---

<PageLayout
  title="HOA Information — Goswick Ranch HOA"
  description="Goswick Ranch HOA governing documents, board information, rules, and meeting minutes."
  pageTitle="HOA Information"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: 'Home', href: `${base}/` },
    { label: 'HOA Information' }
  ]}
>
  <div class="page-content">

    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
      <p>The Goswick Ranch HOA is a self-managed association governed by a volunteer Board of Directors. The Association maintains the gated entrance, enforces the community's CC&amp;Rs and rules, and manages the private roads and common areas within the subdivision.</p>
      <p>The annual assessment is <strong>$216</strong> — one of the lowest HOA fees you'll find for a gated community with private roads in Arizona.</p>
      <p>Arizona law requires us to make governing documents, financial statements, and meeting minutes available to all members. You'll find them all linked below.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">2025 Arizona HOA Law Updates</h2>
      <p>Arizona's legislature passed several updates to the Planned Communities Act (A.R.S. &sect;&sect;&nbsp;33-1801 et seq.) in 2025 that affect all HOAs, including Goswick Ranch:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>SB 1494 — Foreclosure threshold:</strong> An HOA may not pursue foreclosure until assessments are delinquent for at least 18 months <em>or</em> $10,000 (whichever comes first).</li>
        <li><strong>SB 1039 — Meeting recordings:</strong> If a board meeting is recorded, the recording must be retained for 6 months and provided to members upon request.</li>
        <li><strong>SB 1337 — Electronic violations:</strong> Members may now respond to violation notices electronically.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessment cap:</strong> Annual assessment increases exceeding 20% require a majority vote of the membership.</li>
        <li><strong>Annual financial review:</strong> HOAs are required to complete an annual financial audit, review, or compilation within 180 days of the fiscal year end.</li>
        <li><strong>Flag &amp; political sign protections:</strong> Extended to protect display of U.S. flags and political signs as specified in state statute.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-top: var(--space-6); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Architectural Review — Existing Law</h3>
      <p>Under A.R.S. &sect;&nbsp;33-1817 (pre-existing, not a 2025 change): if the Architectural Review Committee does not respond to a <em>complete</em> application within <strong>30 days</strong>, the application is deemed automatically approved by operation of law. Submit a complete application with all required materials to ensure the clock starts running. See <a href={`${base}/hoa/rules/`}>Rules &amp; Regulations</a> for the ARC request process.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <a class="card" href={`${base}/hoa/board/`}>
        <h3>Board of Directors</h3>
        <p>Meet the current volunteer board members who govern the Goswick Ranch HOA.</p>
        <span class="card-cta">View board &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href={`${base}/hoa/documents/`}>
        <h3>CC&amp;Rs &amp; Bylaws</h3>
        <p>Download governing documents — CC&amp;Rs, bylaws, budget, and financial statements.</p>
        <span class="card-cta">View documents &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href={`${base}/hoa/rules/`}>
        <h3>Rules &amp; Regulations</h3>
        <p>Community rules covering property use, construction, and day-to-day standards.</p>
        <span class="card-cta">View rules &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href={`${base}/hoa/minutes/`}>
        <h3>Meeting Minutes</h3>
        <p>Board meeting and annual meeting records, as required by A.R.S. &sect;&nbsp;33-1805.</p>
        <span class="card-cta">View minutes &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="notice" style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">
      <p>Arizona law (A.R.S. &sect;&nbsp;33-1805) requires HOA governing documents, financial statements, and meeting minutes to be reasonably available to all members within 10 business days of a request, at no charge. All required documents on this site are publicly accessible without a login.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</PageLayout>
